rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the types of prizes given in recognition of some sort of achievement. Note that award.award is used for the most general sort of award, e.g. the Nobel Prize, the Academy Awards, the Newbery Medal, etc. For the particular classification of an award, e.g. the Nobel Peace Prize, the Oscar for Best Actor, etc, award.category should be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.award to the mso:award.category in which the award is given. For example, the categories of Nobel Prize include the Nobel Prize in Physics, the Nobel Prize in Literature, the Nobel Peace Prize etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Category
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The category of an award is specific to a particular nomination/conferral of the award, not to the recurring event of the award. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:award.honor.category]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking an award to information about the commendations that were given in the context of the award. For example, in the case of the Newbery Medal, each year one winner is chosen, but several "Honor Books" are also selected.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commendation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking an award to information about the instances in which the award was presented, including the winner, the year, the category, and the ceremony, if there was one.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Honor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award to the next higher award in a hierarchy of awards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Next Higher Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award to the next lower award in a hierarchy of awards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Next Lower Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking an award to information about the instances in which nominations for the award were given, including the nominee, the year, the category, and the ceremony, if there was one.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nomination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.award to the organization or organizations that present or sponsor this award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Presented By

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award to a description of the circumstances under which the award is given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reason Given

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award to a description of the voting system that is used to determine a recipient of the award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Voting System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Retail establishments that sell medals, trophies, and other commemorative objects that indicate an achievement of some sort.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the types of sub-classification of an award. Note that award.award is used for the most general sort of award, e.g. the Nobel Prize, the Academy Awards, the Newbery Medal, etc, while award.category should be used for the particular classification of an award, e.g. the Nobel Peace Prize, the Oscar for Best Actor, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a general award to one of its subclassification, e.g. the Academy Awards and the Academy Award for Best Director.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category to the last calendar year the award was given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Discontinued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category to the date the award was established; this is often different from the date of the first award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Established

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category to the mso:award.discipline that indicates the disciplines or subjects to which this award category relates. E.g., disciplines for the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry might include poetry and literature.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disciplines or subjects

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award category to the first winner of the category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.category to the mso:award.judging_term, which collects the data on a judge's term for a given award category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judges

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award category to the most recent date that the category was awarded.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Awarded

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Many awards have a long list or preliminary list of nominees, from which a short list or final list of nominees are drawn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Long lists

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.category to the mso:award.nominations for the category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nominees

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an award category to the total number of winners of the category at a given time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Winners

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category to the mso:award.presenting_organization that presents or sponsors the category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Presenting Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.category to the mso:award.honor relationships collecting the data on all of the given awards presented/won for the category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winners

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data about the categories used in a recurring ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category in Ceremony Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category_ceremony_type to the mso:award.category used in the ceremonies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category_ceremony_type to date the category was first used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.category_ceremony_type to the date the category was used for the last time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type covers particular events of bestowing an award.award. Some examples are 2002 MTV Music Awards, 2009 MTV Music Awards, 2010 Academy Awards, 2012 Academy Awards, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Ceremony

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.ceremony to the mso:award.honor(s) presented at the ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards Presented

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ceremony to the mso:people.person(s) that hosted the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Host

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an awards ceremony to the work(s) that won the most awards at the ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Most Honored

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an awards ceremony to the work(s) that were nominated for the most awards at the ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Most Nominated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an awards ceremony to information about the number of awards, either nominations or honors, conferred on a particular creative work within a given category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Awards in Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an an awards ceremony to a person who hosted the preshow for the ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preshow Host

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type collecting information about awards other than the overall winner in a competition, e.g. silver medal, honorable mention, award of merit, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commendation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.commendation to its mso:time.recurring_event entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Recurring Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.commendation to its mso:award.category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.commendation to the mso:award.ceremony at which the commendation was presented. Select a specific occurrence of an event rather than the entity that represents a whole series of events (e.g. "2010 Cannes Film Festival" instead of "Cannes Film Festival").
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ceremony

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.commendation to the work for which the commendee won the commendation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commended Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the agent that was commended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commendee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.commendation to the mso:award.competition, if any, for which the commendation is given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.commendation to the name of the commendation that was given, e.g. honorable mention, third place, award of merit, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Title

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.commendation to the date of the commendation. Different awards use different conventions, usually either the year of eligibility or the year presented.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all award competitions. Award competitions are those events in which a winner is chosen from several competitors. Competitions include the 2014 Scripps National Spelling Bee, the 2014 Miss Universe' pageant, and the 2007 Tour de France.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a competition to a television network that broadcast the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Broadcaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a competition to a commendation that is given for the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commendation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.competition to the mso:award.competitor(s) that participated in the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competitors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a competition to an honor that is given for the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Honor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.competition to the mso:award.recurring_competition of which the event is an instance. E.g., if the competition is "Miss Universe 2005", the recurring competition would be "Miss Universe".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a competition to a person who serves or has served as an arbitrator for the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a competition to information about the score assigned by one of the judges in the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a competition to a nomination that is made on the basis of the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nomination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a competition to the competitor that takes second place in the event. Note that this property applies only to competitions that have a second place.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runner Up

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.competition to the mso:award.competition_type of which the competition is a type. For example, season 9 of the television show 'American Idol' has the type 'reality television'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.competition to the mso:award.competitor that won the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all competition types. These are the groupings of competitions that share some characteristics. Examples include 'spelling bee' and 'fishing tournament'
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.competition_type to the mso:award.competition that is of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all competitors in any instance of a competition. These are the agents that participate in a competition with intent to win.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competitor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.competitor to an instance of mso:award.nomination that collects data for a nomination of the agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nominations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.competitor to the mso:award.honor relationship that collects the data for a given award the agent won.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards Won

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a competitor to information about a commendation bestowed on the competitor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commendations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.competitor to the mso:award.competition in which the competitor participated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competitions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.competitor to the mso:mso:award.competition the competitor won.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Won

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all award disciplines. These are the topics of the awards. For example, there are awards specific to 'Irish literature'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Discipline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all Halls of Fame. These are the museums that are dedicated to the individuals and significant contributors in a given area or discipline that are chosen by a committee.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The current address of this hall of fame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Address

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame to the mso:award.hall_of_fame_discipline
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discipline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame to the mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction relationship that collects data on the Hall of Fame's inductions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inductees

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity containing categories of Hall of Fame inductions, like 'performer', 'early influences', and 'lifetime achievement'. Note this type is not a subclass of award.discipline, which is the set of topics for an award, like 'Irish literature'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame Discipline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_discipline to any of the mso:award.hall_of_fame entities that feature the discipline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Halls of Fame

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all Hall of Fame inductees. These are the agents that have been admitted into a Hall of Fame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame Inductee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ahll_of_fame_inductee to the mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction relationship(s) for the given inductee.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame Inductions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for Hall of Fame inductions. Data on this type includes the date of the induction, the inductee, and the category of the induction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame Induction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction to the mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction_category the inductee represents in the induction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction to the date of the induction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction to the Hall of Fame for the induction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction to the inductee of the induction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inductee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of categories used by Halls of Fame to organize its inductees.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall of Fame Induction Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction_category to the mso:award.hall_of_fame_induction relationship(s) that collect the data for Hall of Fame inductions featuring the given category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Inductions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for an award, including the winner, year, the category, and the ceremony, if there was one.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Honor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a person or organization that accepts the award on behalf of the winner, e.g. because the winner was not able to attend the ceremony for some reason.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Acceptor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an mso:award.honor to its mso:time.recurring_event entity. For example, Steve Buscemi's Golden Globe award for Boardwalk Empire is related to the recurring event of Golden Globe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor relationship to its mso:award.category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor to the mso:award.ceremony at which this award was presented. Select a specific occurrence of an event rather than the entity that represents a whole series of events (e.g. "2010 Cannes Film Festival" instead of "Cannes Film Festival").
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ceremony

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor to the mso:award.competition, if any, for which the honor is given.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enter notes such as \"posthumous\" or the official description of the reason for the honor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notes/Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies any nominees that are honored in some way other than as winners, e.g. as honorable mentions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runners-up

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a secondary winning work. A secondary winning work is a creative work that is honored as a proper part of a larger creative work. For example, if a song wins an Academy Award, the movie would be the winning work (the value of the property mso:award.honor.winning_work), but the song would be the value of this property.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Secondary Winning Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a speech that was given by the winner at the ceremony.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speech

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor to its mso:award.winner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor to its mso:award.winning_work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winning Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.honor to the date of the award. Different awards use different conventions, usually either the year of eligibility or the year presented.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all award competition judges. These are the people that participate in award competitions in a judge role.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.judge to the mso:award.judging_term relationship that collects the data on the given judge's tenure judging some awards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards Judged

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the scores assigned by judges with respect to a particular competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a judge of the competition
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the score assigned by the given judge in the given competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for a given judge's term in the judgment of a given award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Judging Term

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.judging_term to the mso:award.category being judged. The category of the award judged is, for example, "Pulitzer Prize for Poetry" rather than simply "Pulitzer Prize"
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.judging_term relationship to the judge for the given award category for the given year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Judge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Can be used for extra information such as "Chair".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Note

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.judging_term to the date the award was given, not the date of the judge's service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person or organization that was long-listed for the award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nominee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enter notes such as \"posthumous\" or the official description of the reason for the honor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notes/Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The year of the award that this long list is for.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all works that have been nominated for any award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award-Nominated Work
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:media_common.creative_work]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.nominated_work to the mso:award.nomination relationship that holds all of the nomination data for the given work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nominations
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this type is needed, it should be added to mso:media_common.creative_work. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for an award nomination. Data for this relationship include the year of the nomination, the nominee, and the category of the nomination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nomination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an mso:award.nomination to its recurring event. For example, a Golden Globe nomination is related to the Golden Globes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to its mso:award.category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to the mso:award.ceremony in which the nominations are revealed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ceremony

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to the mso:award.competition, if any, for which the nomination is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to its mso:award.nominated_work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nominated Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to its mso:award.nominee.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nominee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enter notes such as \"posthumous\" or the official description of the reason for the honor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notes/Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a secondary nominated work. A secondary nominated work is a creative work that is nominated as a proper part of a larger creative work. For example, if a song is nominated for an Academy Award, the movie would be the primary nominated work (the value of the property mso:award.nomination.nominated_work), but the song would be the secondary nominated work (the value of the property mso:award.nomination.secondary_nominated_work).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Secondary Nominated Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.nomination to the date of the nomination. Nominations follow different conventions, usually either the year of eligibility or the year presented.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Abstract entity representing the collection of all award nominees. These are the entities that are nominated for an award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nominee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.nominee to the mso:award.nomination relationship that collects the data for a given nomination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Nominations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that stores information about the number of awards, either honors or nominations, conferred on a particular creative work within a given category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Awards in Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the category of awards for the given creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Creative Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the creative work was only nominated for the award, in which case the property is set to 1. In all other cases, the creative work is assumed to have won the award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nomination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of awards in the given category for the given creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all agents that promote and present awards, e.g. organizations, businesses, countries, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Presenting Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.presenting_organization to the mso:award.category in which the given organization has given awards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Categories Presented

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.presenting_organization to an mso:award.award presented by the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards Presented

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Abstract entity representing the collection of all objects that have been ranked in some manner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranked Item

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranked_item to the mso:award.ranking relationship that collects data about the item's ranking.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranked List Item

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of ranked lists. These are rankings of objects along some characteristic. For example, "100 Greatest Britons" is the ranking of the 100 most influential British people.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranked List

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a ranked list to information about the items that are ranked by the list.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a ranked list to the year that the list was first created.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year Inaugurated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all compilers of ranked lists. These are the agents that rank the list entities according to some characteristics. For example, Forbes is the compiler of the ranked list 'The World's Billionaires'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranked List Compiler

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranked_list_compiler to the mso:award.ranked_list the compiler creates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranked lists

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting data on the ranking for a given item on a given ranked list. Properties include the item, the year, the score, and the list.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.ranking to one of the ranked items in the list.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: item

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranking to the mso:award.ranked_list on which the ranking appears.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: List

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any additional information about this ranking.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Note

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranking relationship to the peak rank the item achieved on the list, for those rolling rankings in which a ranked item might appear in different slots over time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Peak

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranking relationship to the number the ranked item is on the ranked list.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranking to the score that determined the rank.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.ranking to the date of the ranking.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all recurring competitions. These are the event types that recur with some frequency. Entities include 'Project Runway', 'Superbowl', and 'Scripps National Spelling Bee'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.recurring_competition to its individual competitions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Individual Competitions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:award.recurring_competition to the categories that have been or are currently used in its competitions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Categories

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Abstract entity representing the collection of all award winners. These are the subset of award.competitors that win the given competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award Winner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.winner to the mso:award.honor relationship that collects the data for a given award the agent won.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards Won

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Abstract entity representing the collection of award winning works. These are the works that have been nominated and won a given award.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award-Winning Work
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:media_common.creative_work]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:award.winning_work to the mso:award.honor that collects data about the work's awards won.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to mso:media_common.creative_work. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]
